Jomo Kenyatta, the leader of Kanu, deplored regionalism and wanted immediate independence.Because of Kadu’s fears, there were many detailed safeguards in the Majimbo constitution. Mutilating the Kadu-championed Majimbo constitution became a priority for Kanu as Kenya geared towards independence in 1963. 

In 1962, the two parties had been forced into a coalition government under a constitutional framework agreed at the second Lancaster Conference. 

Jomo Kenyatta, the leader of Kanu, deplored regionalism and wanted immediate independence. 



